                <note type="abstract" source="#bib9515-7"><bibl>Luke (Old Syriac Version)<ptr
                    target="http://syriaca.org/work/9515"/></bibl> is the earliest extant
                    translation of <bibl>Luke (literary tradition)<ptr
                        target="http://syriaca.org/work/9648"/></bibl> into Syriac as a "separated Gospel"
                    (not a Gospel harmony). It was probably translated in the 4th or 5th century
                    (though its roots may date to the 3rd), and it predates <bibl>Luke (Peshitta
                        Version)<ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/74"/></bibl>, which
                    ultimately replaced it in the 5th or 6th century.</note>
